definition.value: A bile acid that is 5beta-cholan-24-oic acid bearing three hydroxy substituents at positions 3alpha, 7beta and 12alpha.
A member of the class of muricholic acids in which the hydroxy groups at positions 6 and 7 have beta- and alpha- configuration respectively.
A trihydroxy-5beta-cholanic acid in which the three hydroxy substituents are located at the 3alpha-, 6alpha- and 7alpha-positions.
A monohydroxy-5beta-cholanic acid with a beta-hydroxy substituent at position 3. The 3beta-hydroxy epimer of lithocholic acid.

A trihydroxy-5beta-cholanic acid that is 5beta-cholan-24-oic acid substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 3, 7 and 16 (the 3alpha,7alpha,16alpha stereoisomer). It is a major constituent of the bile of several avian species.
A member of the class of benzochromenones that is 4H-benzo[g]chromen-4-one carrying a methyl group at position 2 and a hydroxy group at positions 5, 6 and 8, respectively.
A flavanone glycoside that is  carthamidin attached to a beta-D-glucopyranosyl residue at position 5 via a glycosidic linkage.
An allo-bile acid that is 5alpha-cholan-24-oic acid bearing two alpha-hydroxy substituents at position 3 and 12.
